SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 934
By Campbell
A RESOLUTION to commend Shafa Abbas for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this legislative body is pleased to recognize certain
persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the
legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Shafa Abbas is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Senator Heidi Campbell; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Abbas's work, her exceptionally personable demeanor, and her
professionalism have resulted in innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted, the
constituents of Senate District 20, and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a student at Vanderbilt University, where she is highly regarded by her
peers, Shafa Abbas has achieved academic success while pursuing a Bachelor of Arts degree
in Public Policy Analysis and Psychology; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Abbas holds several roles on campus, such as PR Chair, Community
Outreach Liaison, and Senior Advisor for the Vanderbilt Pakistani Students Association, as well
as Art Editor for The Vanderbilt Review, Vanderbilt's Undergraduate Literary and Arts Journal;
she has served as a Resident Advisor on campus for two years; and
WHEREAS, she has achieved a number of accomplishments during her academic
career, including being on the Dean's List every semester; she is a recipient of the Crescere
Aude Merit Scholarship and the Nichols Humanitarian Award; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Shafa Abbas brought her many abilities
SJR0934
015447
- 1 -

and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred Fourteenth
General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Abbas has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Shafa Abbas for outstanding
service as a legislative intern for Senator Heidi Campbell and extend to her our best wishes for
every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
